Pre-Game Insights: Jordan Wicks will take the mound for the Cubs in their series finale with the Dodgers on Wednesday.
Jordan Wicks has shown poise beyond his years, posting a solid 4.03 ERA in his first nine major league starts.
Bobby Miller has been inconsistent this season with a 7.79 ERA over 11 games.
The Cubs' bats have been hot lately, led by Cody Bellinger's resurgence and Seiya Suzuki's power surge.
The Dodgers have been nearly unbeatable at Dodger Stadium this season.
Bobby Miller's electric fastball, which averaged 98.3 mph in his last start, remains a potent weapon.
The Dodgers' lineup includes Shohei Ohtani, Mookie Betts, and Freddie Freeman, presenting a significant challenge for Jordan Wicks.
The Cubs are in the thick of a tight NL Wild Card race, adding motivation for the game.
The Dodgers are in a tight race for the best record in the National League, adding motivation for the game.
